            <text_ee58
                jcr:created="{Date}2017-03-29T22:43:35.909Z"
                jcr:createdBy="lsloane"
                jcr:lastModified="{Date}2017-07-07T19:47:03.657Z"
                jcr:lastModifiedBy="lsloane"
                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                sling:resourceType="beagle/components/text"
                text="&lt;h3>Supporting developers and professionals&lt;br>&#xa;&lt;/h3>&#xa;&lt;h3>&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h3>&#xa;&lt;div class=&quot;text-5-block&quot;>&lt;span class=&quot;text-light&quot;>From Windows to Office productivity tools, Microsoft solutions are industry standards used by leading organizations worldwide. One reason Microsoft remains a global leader is its strong community and loyal customers who connect with the company and with each other through many web portals. Sites such as Docs.Microsoft.com, Azure.com, Microsoft Developers Network (MSDN), TechNet, and VisualStudio.com provide resources, discussion forums, and support for developers and IT professionals.&lt;/span>&lt;/div>&#xa;&lt;div class=&quot;text-5-block&quot;>&lt;span class=&quot;text-light&quot;>&lt;br>&#xa;“We have 800 authors and 5 million articles on our MSDN, TechNet, VisualStudio.com, and &amp;nbsp;Docs.Microsoft.com web portals,” says Mary McHale, Principal Group Manager at Microsoft. “In total, &amp;nbsp;we reach about 90 million developers and IT professionals through these portals. A community this size &amp;nbsp;is a huge asset to our brand. If we can mobilize and inspire people to stay involved in Microsoft products, we can continue to grow our brand and keep it strong.”&lt;/span>&lt;/div>&#xa;"/>
            <pullquote_f049
                jcr:created="{Date}2017-03-27T18:44:02.724Z"
                jcr:createdBy="lsloane"
                jcr:lastModified="{Date}2017-07-07T19:48:16.450Z"
                jcr:lastModifiedBy="lsloane"
                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                sling:resourceType="beagle/components/pullquote"
                author="Gigel Avram"
                fontstyle="italic"
                quote="Since adding Livefyre, we’ve seen an increase in quality comments and a 10% to 30% improvement in customer satisfaction."
                title="Principal Data Science Manager, Microsoft"/>
            <text_86ac
                jcr:created="{Date}2017-02-23T17:14:47.284Z"
                jcr:createdBy="wmyersta"
                jcr:lastModified="{Date}2017-07-07T19:49:01.353Z"
                jcr:lastModifiedBy="lsloane"
                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                sling:resourceType="beagle/components/text"
                text="&lt;div class=&quot;text-5-block&quot;>&lt;span class=&quot;text-light&quot;>Microsoft found that articles with high community interaction were associated with higher customer satisfaction; that meant providing visitors with a modern commenting solution was a must. But, the question became scalability—how to effectively manage comments and interact with tens of millions of readers with less than a thousand article owners.&lt;/span>&lt;/div>&#xa;&lt;div class=&quot;text-5-block&quot;>&lt;span class=&quot;text-light&quot;>&lt;br>&#xa;Commenting solutions could improve the customer experience, but only Livefyre, part of Adobe Experience Manager within Adobe Marketing Cloud, gave Microsoft the tools to be able to put in place a scalable business workflow for developers to comment inline or in the discussion threads and support reliable comment analysis and management.&lt;/span>&lt;br>&#xa;&lt;/div>&#xa;&lt;div class=&quot;text-5-block&quot;>&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div>&#xa;"/>
