            <text_4293
                jcr:created="{Date}2017-02-23T17:19:06.983Z"
                jcr:createdBy="wmyersta"
                jcr:lastModified="{Date}2017-07-07T20:02:51.086Z"
                jcr:lastModifiedBy="lsloane"
                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                sling:resourceType="beagle/components/text"
                text="&lt;div class=&quot;text-5-block&quot;>&lt;span class=&quot;text-light&quot;>In the past, the need for article changes—such as correcting details so that an article matches a product experience—might have gone unnoticed. Now they can be addressed quickly and before other customers encounter them. “The key for this is enabling the business workflow and engaging a large number of our engineers, who are also authors, to listen to customers, connect, and address issues in a timely manner,” says Avram.&lt;/span>&lt;/div>&#xa;&lt;div class=&quot;text-5-block&quot;>&lt;span class=&quot;text-light&quot;>&lt;br>&#xa;By encouraging higher quality conversations and more response from article owners, Microsoft is building a stronger community. Users who participate in Livefyre comments are nine times more likely to contribute to articles in GitHub, so encouraging active conversations in the comments can have a long-term effect on the Microsoft brand.&lt;/span>&lt;/div>&#xa;&lt;div class=&quot;text-5-block&quot;>&lt;span class=&quot;text-light&quot;>&lt;br>&#xa;“If developers don’t have the support they need, they may lose interest in developing for Microsoft solutions,” says Avram. “To keep our brand strong, we need to support our community through good experiences and high engagement. Customers expect an interactive experience, to be listened to, and that their concerns are addressed in a timely manner. Livefyre gives us the tools to make our content better and improve customer satisfaction.”&lt;/span>&lt;/div>&#xa;&lt;div class=&quot;text-5-block&quot;>&lt;span class=&quot;text-light&quot;>&lt;br>&#xa;&lt;strong>Vision for the future&lt;/strong>&lt;br>&#xa;Adobe and Microsoft have recently come together in a long-term strategic partnership to help enterprises accelerate digital transformation. Combining the power of Adobe Experience Cloud solutions, the Microsoft Azure Cloud platform, and Microsoft business applications such as Dynamics 365, the two companies will help organizations leverage synergies across systems and deliver compelling, personalized experiences through every phase of their customer relationships to strengthen their brands.&lt;/span>&lt;br>&#xa;&lt;/div>&#xa;"/>
